Sheet1.Setters_Comment: A trick &lit — The theme often holds the meaning of the piece of work you are considering, the wordplay also denotes a hidden word, where you can find THEME in (THE ME)aning

Sheet1.Clue: You get in a spot and mouth off (5)
Sheet1.Tooltip_1: Fodder: These words need to be used in some way to make up your answer. 'you' gives the letter U to insert
Sheet1.Tooltip_2: Wordplay: 'get in' indicates insertion
Sheet1.Tooltip_3: Fodder: These words need to be used in some way to make up your answer. 'spot' provides S P O T for the outer letters
Sheet1.Setters_Comment: Here we put YOU (U) inside SPOT to make SPOUT, which is to mouth off.

Sheet1.Clue: Delight with an uplifting story and a nice ending (5)

Sheet1.Tooltip_2: Wordplay: 'uplifting' indicates reversing the following word

Sheet1.Tooltip_4: Fodder: These words need to be used in some way to make up your answer. The ending of 'nice' is E

Sheet1.Clue: Sat up first, to eat a bite (5)

Sheet1.Tooltip_3: Wordplay: 'first' indicates taking the first letters of the next two words
Sheet1.Tooltip_4: Fodder: These words need to be used in some way to make up your answer. Taking the first letters of 'to' and 'eat' gives TE
Sheet1.Setters_Comment: Here we put SAT upwards (TAS) with the first letters of TO EAT (T)(E) together to make TASTE, which is a bite.

Sheet1.Clue: Overtake lead stallion to secure post (5)
Sheet1.Tooltip_1: Wordplay: Overtake is a bit of a misdirection, this is a down clue so this is telling you to put something "over" TAKE

Sheet1.Tooltip_3: Fodder: These words need to be used in some way to make up your answer.  What is the first letter of STALLION?
Sheet1.Setters_Comment: Here we take the lead of STALLION (S) and put it over TAKE (it’s a down clue: ‘overtake’ = S over TAKE) to make STAKE, which is a secure post.

Sheet1.Clue: Are leaves out of the east mulched to make this? (5)

Sheet1.Tooltip_3: Wordplay: 'mulched' indicates an anagram

Sheet1.Setters_Comment: Here we remove E from LEAVES and anagram toto make SALVE, a cryptic def and semi &lit this whole clue means SALVE.
